title: Show HN: AlpacApp – An Extendable and Highly Customizable Website Builder
text:
Hey HN, I'm Yassine and today I'm launching AlpacApp (formerly yawb.io), a modern website builder with four distinctive qualities:

1. With a single click, you can export your project as a Zip file and host it yourself if you wish.

2. You have full control over the design of the website. Click on any element and start customizing the styling properties.

3. You can create your own blocks to extend the functionality of AlpacApp. You can even, download, share and upload blocks.

4. It features a built-in Notion integration to embed your notion pages directly in your website. Write in Notion and Design in AlpacApp.

I truly believe in this project and while there are already plenty of website builders available out there, none of them provides the level of customizability and flexibility that Alpac.App provides!

I'm really open to feedback and any requests. You can follow my build in public journey on twitter: https://twitter.com/ybouane

Yassine

Ask HN: Anyone Replace Jira with GitHub Issues?
text:
I'm wanting to centralize tickets & documentation in Github, and in the process eliminate Jira & Notion.

Question: Is it possible to create tickets for a repo without granting read access to code?

If not, is the work around to create a repo just for tickets that everyone has access to? Is it even practical at this point?

Has anyone successfully pulled this off at their org?

Show HN: You-tldr-Summarize and Interact with YouTube Videos in your language
text:
Last weekend, my brother and I sat spent some time revamping one of our older products, you-tldr (https://you-tldr.com/) to the latest and greatest foundational models. We launched on HN back then, so I figured we'd do it again.

The front end is made with Vercel and Tailwind, and the backend is a mixture of GCP Cloud Functions and a Fly.io FastAPI that utilizes LangChain and OpenAI GPT-3.5-turbo API to do the summary and chatbot.

The product itself is 10x better: You can now get a concise summary of any video in seconds, and even ask questions about it in the Q&A chat window. No more wasted time slogging through long videos to find the information you need!

Feedback and comments welcome!

title: Ask HN: Just installed a custom Android ROM in my old smartphone – now what?
text:
You have that old smartphone kept in a drawer. One day you decide you want to install a newer OS on it because it is stuck on Android 7 or something. Not that the phone was being used anyway, but why not? It's Sunday and you're bored.

After lots of research and work, you finally make it, and it's delightful: your old phone is fast again, and bloatware free. This was fun!

But... Then what? What creative uses can you come up with for your old Android phone that is now new again, given that you already have a newer phone for your regular use?
